Cell.Text: [S] I don't really want to talk about that right now.

I've been following the Riddle'Thar for most my life, but it's been hard to feel a close connection with them. | The North is my home, but it's also so far from any centers of the Riddle'Thar's worship. | I came to Skyrim to establish a temple in honor of the Riddle'Thar. I intend to live there and spend my days revering them.

[S] My 'ma and 'pa found me in a shipwreck. They didn't know anything of Khajiit, but they still took me in. | They'd always wanted a child, said I was a gift from Kyne or something. When I was old enough they decided they wanted me to learn about my heritage. | They got me a tutor all the way from Cyrodiil, she was Khajiit, like me. Taught me everything I know about the Riddle'Thar and my culture. | Tried to teach me Ta'agra and "proper" speak, could never get it, words felt weird in my mouth. Anyway, I'm as much Khajiit as I am Nord.

[S] Oh it's the most beautiful place, a little slice of Nordic life that's all my own. | The village I grew up in is called Kyne's Perch, it's a sleepy little fishing town in the south of the island. | However, the big money is made in the mines up north. That's why the East Empire Company has an office on the island. | Augh, talking about this is making me homesick.
Away and bile your head.

Her name was Jah'alaka, she was strict and unforgiving but is also a big reason that I am who I am today. I have a lot to thank her for. | I'll be honest, I didn't like her at first but when she started discussing Khajiiti culture I gote entralled. It opened my eyes as to who I am. | My favorite lessons covered the old Khajiiti tales, she had a way of spinning those stories into breathtaking tapestries of song. I love it. | I hope to see her again some day. It's been so long since we last talked.

Some call it a god, but the Riddle'Thar is more a set of guidelines that Khajiit try to live by. | "First, a true cat must be curious.One must always listen longer and gaze deeper." | "Next, a true cat must be clever. When trapped in life's cruel maze, you must resist the call to simple solutions." | "Third, a true cat must treat themselves with kindness. Too few. I tell you, the fruit of charity grows from joyful, vigorous branches." | "Finally, a true cat must be wary. Be cautious. Move swiftly. Hide your hearts away in the thick jungles of the self." | These are the virtues that all Khajiiti must abide by if we are to make it to the Sands Behind the Stars.
Okay!
[S] Right! Off we go, then.
[S] Sure. See ye around.
[S] Off to start a bit of trouble, are we?
[S] Oh, I suppose I could manage that.

[S] G|Meet you back home then.
Sure! What's on your mind?

Ah, my 'da is the best. He works for the East Empire Company, he's away a lot on expeditions but he always brings me back little gifts from abroad. | My 'ma thinks he's too soft on me, well I think she's too hard on me!

'Ma and I didn't see eye-to-eye for a long time. We're both stubborn and willful. I bonded with my 'da a lot growing up and often neglected 'ma. | Looking back on it now I know she really just wanted what was best for me. Sometimes I wish I could go back and change things between us.
Nah, an only child. I made a few really close friends when I was older though.
[S] Shut it with that racist jabber. I was raised by Nord parents on Kottheim since I was a wee cub. | Do you really think I'd talk like them milkdrinkers down south just because I'm a Khajiit?
